  "body": "<!--ðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž\r\n\r\nHellooo! ðŸ˜„ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž-->\r\n\r\n# ðŸ’Ž Issue\r\n\r\n### Background\r\nPrysm uses 2 flags to help identify where to store certain cached items ( such as valdiator.db,auth-token, terms of service acceptance, etc). the user experience is not very clear when to use one or the other and should be looked into how to safely manage or document for the future.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\ncurrent state of things \r\n- If a walletdir is provided then it will be used to store the validator db\r\n- if a datadir is provided it will override the walletdir location, but only if it's a different path from the default datadir path\r\n- Terms of Service acceptance file ( file required to skip user prompt  for agreements) only uses the datadir path instead of a provided walletdir path\r\n- walletdir also sets the root for the keymanager type path ",
